  "content": "    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\">\n    <p>The embedding backend everyone benchmarks? It's less than 10% of the real-world latency. In a RAG pipeline, the retrieval layer — not the model — is what your users actually wait for.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">03 / 08</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- SLIDE 4: THE NUMBERS — bar chart -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">The Numbers</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"margin-bottom: 16px;\">\n    Per-Embed Latency<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-green\">Across All Inputs</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 19px; margin-bottom: 32px;\">\n    Lower is better. Each bar = mean of 5 runs. Error bars omitted for clarity\n    (all &le; &plusmn;11ms).\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Short texts -->\n  <div style=\"margin-bottom: 28px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 12px;\">Short Texts (2-3 words &times; 5)</div>\n    <div class=\"bar-row\">\n      <div class=\"bar-label\" style=\"color: var(--accent-amber);\">CPU</div>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill\" style=\"width: 100%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(245,158,11,0.3), rgba(245,158,11,0.6));\">\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"bar-value\" style=\"color: var(--accent-amber);\">527 ms</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"bar-row\">\n      <div class=\"bar-label\" style=\"color: var(--accent-cyan);\">Intel iGPU</div>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill\" style=\"width: 9.7%; background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(6,182,212,0.4), rgba(6,182,212,0.8));\">\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"bar-value\" style=\"color: var(--accent-cyan);\">51 ms</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"bar-row\">\n      <div clas